dxc4 13. bxc4 Be7 14. Ng2 c5 $1 15. dxc5 a5 $1 $11 {[%cal Yf6d7,Yd7c5,Gb8c6]})
{Black could have taken the initiative now by means of} 11... g5 $1 12. Ng2 h5
$1 {when White is suddenly under pressure, for instance:} 13. gxh5 Nxh5 {
[%cal Yh5g3]} 14. Kf2 g4 $1 15. Rc1 (15. fxg4 Nf6 $36) 15... Bxb3 16. axb3 gxf3
17. Kxf3 Nd7 $15 {and Black has better chances due to the superior structure
and safer king's position.}) 7. f3 (7. Qxb7 $6 {can be dangerous due to} e5 $1
8. dxe5 Nc5 $3 9. Qxc6+ Nfd7 {[%cal Ga8c8,Yd8h4] when White might have more
