development and puts some pressure on Black's queenside, now exposed due to
the bishop's absence. The inclusion of f2-f3 may be useful for White in some
cases, as it ensures the better central control and restrains the Nf6. The
most important decision for White here is whether to castle kingside or
queenside (or abstain from castling altogether!). In order to make things
simple and organized, I decided to split the content into two chapters. Let's
start with the safe and positional approach that features kingside castling.} (
{Let's examine some different move orders for White, having in mind that Qb3
