{Black has an important move in this position. What is it?} 20... Qe8 $1 {
[%csl Gg6] This simple queen move is good for many reasons. The first of them
is that by protecting the bishop Black avoids the exchange on d3, which would
help White to bring the knight back into the game.} 21. h3 Bd8 $1 {[%csl Yd4,
Yf4][%cal Gf6d8,Gd8c7,Gc7b6,Gf8f1] The second and perhaps most important idea
is to prepare this maneuver. The dark-squared bishop can still attack d4 from
b6, but now Black is also able to put pressure on f4. Also, Black is able to
develop all his pieces now despite his space shortage.} 22. Rd1 Bc7 23. Rd2 {
[%cal Yd2e2,Ye2f2]} Qf7 24. Rdf2 Rae8 $13 {Sasikiran,K (2681)-Wang,Y (2709)
